- [LUKE]: Uh-huh.

01:27:21.050 --> 01:27:23.218
- [MARTIN]: Just like in regulation.
- [LUKE]: Yeah.

01:27:23.219 --> 01:27:26.012
- [MARTIN]: Lob wedge.
- [LUKE]: Thank you.

01:27:26.639 --> 01:27:29.266
[BRANDEL]: This is the same shot
he had just a few moments ago,

01:27:29.267 --> 01:27:32.269
however, the situation
is entirely different.

01:27:32.270 --> 01:27:36.147
He knows that given T.K. Oh's lie,
he could win this tournament.

01:27:36.148 --> 01:27:37.440
Whereas a few moments ago,

01:27:37.441 --> 01:27:38.857
he was chasing.

01:27:44.906 --> 01:27:45.823
[LUKE]: See it.

01:27:47.450 --> 01:27:48.492
Feel it.

01:27:50.120 --> 01:27:51.161
And trust it.

01:28:00.297 --> 01:28:02.715
[cheers and applause]

01:28:02.716 --> 01:28:04.925
[KELLY]: Not quite like
his hole out in regulation,

01:28:04.926 --> 01:28:06.885
but under the circumstances,
a very solid shot.

01:28:06.886 --> 01:28:10.388
[BRANDEL]: If T.K. Oh was looking for
a gift from an inexperienced Luke,

01:28:10.389 --> 01:28:11.764
he didn't get it.

01:28:11.765 --> 01:28:14.767
T.K. Oh a nearly impossible pitch.

01:28:14.768 --> 01:28:16.185
He's looking at a tight flag,

01:28:16.186 --> 01:28:17.812
the green is running away from him,

01:28:17.813 --> 01:28:19.772
not to mention the water.

01:28:19.773 --> 01:28:22.859
Anything short of hitting that flagstick
and he's probably going swimming.

01:28:22.860 --> 01:28:24.068
[BRANDEL]:
Plain and simple here, Kelly.

01:28:24.069 --> 01:28:25.695
He needs to play away from the hole.

01:28:25.696 --> 01:28:29.073
And it's a pretty safe bet that he's
gonna have a longer birdie putt...

01:28:29.074 --> 01:28:30.408
than Luke's 8-footer.

01:28:30.409 --> 01:28:32.827
[KELLY]:
The ultimate test for T.K. Oh,

01:28:32.828 --> 01:28:35.121
but I wouldn't put it past him.
He's done it before.

01:28:36.248 --> 01:28:37.497
[BRANDEL]: Look at the way
he's sizing this up.

01:28:37.498 --> 01:28:38.665
It almost looks like...

01:28:38.666 --> 01:28:40.167
and he is, I think,

01:28:40.168 --> 01:28:41.209
gonna go right at this hole.

01:28:41.210 --> 01:28:42.919
This absolutely makes no sense to me.

01:28:42.920 --> 01:28:44.713
If he doesn't hole this,

01:28:44.714 --> 01:28:47.090
it's very likely that this ball's
gonna run off of the green.

01:28:47.091 --> 01:28:48.633
[KELLY]: This would really
be something.

01:28:48.634 --> 01:28:51.678
He's got to aim
right for the flagstick.

01:28:51.679 --> 01:28:55.557
Anything short of perfect here,
he's looking at bogie at best.

01:28:55.558 --> 01:28:57.017
That's if he's lucky enough
to avoid the water.

01:28:57.769 --> 01:29:00.395
[BRANDEL]: The only way
to pull this shot off on that line...

01:29:00.396 --> 01:29:02.314
