01:29:02.315 --> 01:29:06.108
and he has to land it in an area
about as big as a dinner plate.

01:29:17.412 --> 01:29:19.330
[KELLY]: And it looks good.

01:29:22.417 --> 01:29:24.168
It's got a chance.

01:29:25.003 --> 01:29:25.878
[crowd groans]

01:29:25.879 --> 01:29:27.588
Didn't go in. Remarkable!

01:29:27.589 --> 01:29:29.590
[BRANDEL]: He's unlucky, Kelly,
that that ball didn't go in,

01:29:29.591 --> 01:29:31.634
but lucky
that it stayed on the green...

01:29:31.635 --> 01:29:34.595
and gave him about
a 15-foot putt up the hill,

01:29:34.596 --> 01:29:36.596
and maybe he can put
the pressure on Luke.

01:29:36.597 --> 01:29:39.599
[KELLY]: And look at him.
He's not even fazed.

01:29:39.600 --> 01:29:43.144
This is a makeable putt for T.K. Oh.

01:29:43.145 --> 01:29:44.813
Is this where experience pays off?

01:29:44.814 --> 01:29:47.690
[BRANDEL]: Generally speaking,
first-in in a playoff wins.

01:29:47.691 --> 01:29:49.859
And if he makes this, I promise you,

01:29:49.860 --> 01:29:52.070
that hole will look a lot smaller to Luke.

01:29:56.450 --> 01:29:59.869
[KELLY]: How many times has T.K. Oh
been in this exact spot...

01:29:59.870 --> 01:30:01.996
