01:30:16.886 --> 01:30:18.178
[KELLY]: He thought
he had that one.

01:30:18.179 --> 01:30:21.348
[BRANDEL]: T.K. Oh's tee shot
left him with a lot of stress.

01:30:21.349 --> 01:30:23.600
His second shot left him
with a lot of work.

01:30:23.601 --> 01:30:25.727
And now it's Luke
who has the work to do,

01:30:25.728 --> 01:30:28.772
and T.K. Oh no longer has control
of his own fate.

01:30:28.773 --> 01:30:31.358
That control lies with Luke Chisolm.

01:30:33.694 --> 01:30:37.864
[KELLY]: It was a great par
for T.K. Oh just to stay in it.

01:30:37.865 --> 01:30:39.407
But now the door is open...

01:30:39.867 --> 01:30:42.910
for Luke Chisolm
to win the Texas Open.

01:30:42.911 --> 01:30:44.328
[BRANDEL]:
One can only imagine...

01:30:44.329 --> 01:30:46.789
what's going on in the mind
of Luke Chisolm right now.

01:30:46.790 --> 01:30:49.125
Two weeks ago his career was over,

01:30:49.126 --> 01:30:52.628
and now he is one putt away
from taking the Texas Open...

01:30:52.629 --> 01:30:55.631
and beating the best player in golf
in the process.

01:31:17.028 --> 01:31:18.737
[no dialogue]

01:31:26.287 --> 01:31:30.332
[JOHNNY]: Luke knew this putt
was meaningless...

01:31:30.333 --> 01:31:31.499
